Kim Yong Nam Meets Mongolian Government Economic Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, met and had a friendly talk with the Mongolian government economic delegation headed by Ya. Sodbaatar, vice-minister of Industry and Trade, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Ri Myong San, vice-minister of Foreign Trade, officials concerned and the Mongolian ambassador to the DPRK.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Mongolian Government Economic Delegation  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the visiting Mongolian government economic delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, by Ya. Sodbaatar, vice-minister of Industry and Trade, who is head of the delegation on Oct. 9.

3rd Pyongyang Autumn International Trade Fair Goes on 
